text: 150 (one hundred fifty) is a whole number. It comes after 149 and before 151. == In mathematics == *150 is an even number, because it can be divided by 2. *150 can be factored into prime numbers as 2×3×5×5. == In other areas == *The number of degrees in the quincunx astrological aspect explored by Johannes Kepler. *The approximate value for Dunbar's number, a theoretical value with implications in sociology and anthropology Category:Integers
title: 150 (number)
